<s> (11/17/1998) While people around the world watched the beginning of the best meteor storm light show in three decades, the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space Administration and private satellite companies rotated their high-tech machinery to face away from the approaching debris. </s>
<s> (11/17/1998) The shower, which peaks every 33 years, is caused by the Earth's passage through the long tail of the Comet Tempel-Tuttle. </s>
